  "prompt": "What is the oldest book ever written?",
  "response": "The oldest known written book is generally considered to be the \"Epic of Gilgamesh,\" a Sumerian epic poem that was written on clay tablets around 2100 BCE. The most complete version of the epic was discovered in the library of the Assyrian king Ashurbanipal in Nineveh, dating back to around 1200 BCE. The \"Epic of Gilgamesh\" is considered one of the earliest great works of literature and is an important source of information about the culture and beliefs of ancient Mesopotamia.",
